HEADWORD: Farraginous
<hw>Far*rag*i*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Farrago</er>.]</ety> <def>Formed of various materials; mixed;
<as>as, a <ex>farraginous</ex> mountain</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Kirwan.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>farraginous</qex> concurrence of all conditions, tempers,
